{"title":"Marin Expands Alcatraz Dirt Jump Line to Include $899 Rigid-Fork Option","link":"https://theradavist.com/marin-alcatraz-dirt-jump-bike/","date":1721908848000,"content":"<p>If you’ve ever thought about getting into (or <i>back</i> into) some BMX shenanigans once in a while, now might be the time. Marin just expanded their Alcatraz dirt jump / pumptrack bike lineup to include a fully rigid option for $899. That’s $100 less than the fully rigid dirt jumper YT just launched, but you can buy the Alcatraz at an actual bike shop!<span></span></p>\n<p><img width=\"2000\" height=\"1125\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/marin-alcatraz-dirt-jumper-radavist-1.jpg?fit=1200,1125&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/marin-alcatraz-dirt-jumper-radavist-1.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/marin-alcatraz-dirt-jumper-radavist-1.jpg?resize=1200,675&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/marin-alcatraz-dirt-jumper-radavist-1.jpg?resize=768,432&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/marin-alcatraz-dirt-jumper-radavist-1.jpg?resize=1536,864&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p>The Alcatraz 1 has an alloy frame and a suspension-corrected, tapered-steerer cro-mo fork so you can plug in a 100 mm suspension fork down the road if you want. The only other cost-cutting measure is the cable-actuated Tektro front and rear disc brakes.</p>\n<p><img width=\"2000\" height=\"1125\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/marin-alcatraz-dirt-jumper-radavist-4.jpg?fit=1200,1125&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/marin-alcatraz-dirt-jumper-radavist-4.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/marin-alcatraz-dirt-jumper-radavist-4.jpg?resize=1200,675&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/marin-alcatraz-dirt-jumper-radavist-4.jpg?resize=768,432&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/marin-alcatraz-dirt-jumper-radavist-4.jpg?resize=1536,864&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p>But if you’d rather go higher-end out of the box, the Alcatraz 2 gets hydraulic Shimano MT201 brakes and a coil-sprung Manitou Circus Expert fork for $1,399.</p>\n<p><img width=\"2000\" height=\"1125\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/marin-alcatraz-dirt-jumper-radavist-3.jpg?fit=1200,1125&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/marin-alcatraz-dirt-jumper-radavist-3.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/marin-alcatraz-dirt-jumper-radavist-3.jpg?resize=1200,675&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/marin-alcatraz-dirt-jumper-radavist-3.jpg?resize=768,432&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/marin-alcatraz-dirt-jumper-radavist-3.jpg?resize=1536,864&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /> <img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1125\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/marin-alcatraz-dirt-jumper-radavist-5.jpg?fit=1200,1125&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/marin-alcatraz-dirt-jumper-radavist-5.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/marin-alcatraz-dirt-jumper-radavist-5.jpg?resize=1200,675&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/marin-alcatraz-dirt-jumper-radavist-5.jpg?resize=768,432&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/07/marin-alcatraz-dirt-jumper-radavist-5.jpg?resize=1536,864&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p>There are also frame-only kits for $549. Every Alcatraz is available in a short (385 mm reach) and a long (430 mm reach), and runs on slotted 135×10 rear axles, 73mm threaded bottom brackets, and of course, 26” wheels.</p>\n<p>See more at <a href=\"https://www.marinbikes.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Marin</a></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/marin-alcatraz-dirt-jump-bike/\">Marin Expands Alcatraz Dirt Jump Line to Include $899 Rigid-Fork Option</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theradavist.com\">The Radavist</a>.</p>","author":"Travis Engel","siteTitle":"The Radavist","siteHash":"96eb481d8084f04a4602bac57874ba717baf56b758f45547b5caf2312da766ef","entryHash":"aea25e289b1bc2bbdfe0a7ff6eec8e7084a3446bc3dbaea73991c0f90a946ed5","category":"Cycling"}